reviewText:
Now, This may sound like a biased review since some people know I know the developer of this game in real life... (Grew up together).

I remember when he first told me he was creating this game for steam... It used to be a HTML 5 game that he made about 3 years back using Construct 2. I remember being in awe at the complexity of the game and how freaking awesome it was with the mechanics! I was so excited for him (And I still am now) I never thought he would legetimately make it to the steam store but as always, he has blown me away with this incredible game!

If you like games like Super Meat Boy... Be prepared for a whole new world to punch your monitor over!!! I had the pleasure of bug testing this game before it's release and I was able to play the game during it's alpha stages as well. The game was so much fun at all stages of it's creation and kept me wanting more!

- Fast paced? {Check}
- Frustrating? {Check}
- Awesome eye popping indie graphics? {Check}
- Awesome music? {Check}
- Wish you had more time to play for hours on end? {Check}
- Amazing use of game mechanics? {Check}
- Kawaii main characters? {Check}

I could go on and on with that list but hey! Find out for yourself! I mean, 10 bucks is cheap for this game... I would pay more for it!

The only negative... I broke a key on my keayboard during gameplay... (Still have not told the dev about it).
